                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1r">f. 1r</locus>
                           <desc>-v: Excerpt from a theological treatise (?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>: በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ፩አምላክ፡
                              ይቤሎሙ፡ አባዊነ፡ ቅዱሳን፡ አርአዮሙ፡ ኅቡአቲሁ፡ ወመንክራቲሁ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> The text is partly abraded, partly readable on
                              <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>
                           <note>. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#2r">f. 2r</locus>
                           <desc>-v: ʾAsmat-prayer (?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> In Amharic. Crudely written. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#65v">f. 65v-67</locus>
                           <desc>v: Excerpt from a hymn to St Mary (?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#65v">65v</locus>: ዕፅልምልት፡ እምኢቄም፡ ወሐና፡ ዘፈረደኪ፡ በቅዱስ፡
                              መሶበ፡ ወርቅ፡ አንቲ፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> Very crudely written in the bottom margins of
                              <locus target="#65v">65v</locus>
                           <note>, 66r and 67v, in the same hand as Additiones 4, 5 and 7. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#103v">f. 103v</locus>
                           <desc>: Hymn to St Mary. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#103v">103v</locus>: ኵሎሙ፡ ሠራዊተ፡ መላእክት፡ መንፈሳውያን። አርባበ፡
                              ሰማያት፡ ነቢቦሙ፡ ኪሩቤል፡...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Very crudely written in the same hand as Additiones 3, 5 and 7.
                              Some parts of it have been erased. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#121r">f. 121r</locus>
                           <desc>: Excerpt from a hymn to St Gabrǝʾel (?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#121r">121r</locus>: ዳዊት፡ ነቢይ፡ በስመ፡ ፀለየ፡ እጼሊ፡ ኀቤከ፡
                              እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላኪየ፡ እንዘ፡ እብል፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The prayer is very crudely written in the same hand as Additiones
                              3, 4 and 7. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <locus target="#121v">f. 121v</locus>
                           <desc>: Calendaric note listing the feasts dedicated to the
                              Apostles.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#121v">121v</locus>: ሠረቀ፡ መስከረም፡ አመ፡ ፩በርተሎሜዎስ፡
                              ሐዋርያ።…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is written in a careful hand. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a7">
                           <locus target="#121v">f. 121v-122</locus>
                           <desc>v: Excerpt from a salām-hymn (?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#121v">121v</locus>: ሰላም፡ ለአብ፡ ለወልድ፡ ቃለ፡ ወለመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡
                              ሰላም፡ ዘአካሎሙ፡ አካሉ፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The prayer is very crudely written in the same hand as Additiones
                              3, 4 and 5 </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a8">
                           <locus target="#122r">f. 122r</locus>
                           <desc>: Ownership note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#122r">122r</locus>: ዝዳዊት፡ ዝገብረ፡ ጻድቃን፡ ዘተሳየጦ፡ በንዋዩ፡
                              ዘሰረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በስልጣን፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note mentions Gabra Ṣādǝqān as the owner of the Ms. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The Pss. are divided into groups of ten separated by a
                           line of alternating black and red dots. 
 - The midpoint of the
                           “Psalms of David” (in P<locus target="#77">77</locus>) is marked on
                              <locus target="#48v">48v</locus> with an inscription in Amharic ኩሌታ
                           (?): የዳዊት፡ አ.
 - Part of the line is taken up: e.g., <locus target="#3v">3v</locus>, 5v, 15v, 30r, 40r, 56v, 83r, 105v.
 -
                           Part of the line is taken down: <locus target="#20v">20v</locus>, 92v,
                           121r. 
 - Unreadable and mostly erased notes: <locus target="#2v">2v</locus>, 3v.
 - Pen trials or writing exercises (from
                           unidentified prayers to Mary): <locus target="#103v">103v</locus>.</item>
                     </list>
